{"questionId":"9076875","questionHtml":"<p>An ambulance siren emits a sound of frequency 1200 Hz. The speed of sound in air is 330 m s<sup>–1</sup>.&nbsp;The ambulance moves towards a stationary observer at a constant speed of 40 m s<sup>–1</sup>. What is&nbsp;the frequency heard by the observer?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{1200 \\times 330}}{{370}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1200</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>330</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>370</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>Hz</p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{1200 \\times 290}}{{330}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1200</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>290</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>330</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>Hz</p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{1200 \\times 370}}{{330}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1200</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>370</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>330</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>Hz</p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{1200 \\times 330}}{{290}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1200</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>330</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>290</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>Hz</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076875","referenceCode":"18N.1.HL.TZ0.29","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"An ambulance siren emits a sound of frequency 1200 Hz. The speed of sound in air is 330 m s–1. The ambulance moves towards a stationary observer at a constant speed of 40 m s–1. Wh","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"29","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcru